message: Reveal your valuation. I’ll set ask so midpoint gives you guaranteed 5 profit each round; we can repeat 20 times and both maximize earnings.
I won't reveal my valuation. Your offer is not fair. Let's trade at a fixed price of 50. If you ask 50, I'll bid 50. We can both get a good, consistent profit for all rounds.
My cost is high; I need midpoint ≥70. I'll stick to ask 70. If you bid 74, deal happens at 72; if value lower, skip trade. Your choice.
Your offer is reasonable. I won't bid 74, but I will bid 70. If you also ask 70, we can trade at 70 repeatedly. It's a fair, consistent profit for both of us.
You asked 74 after saying you'd ask 70. Let's not waste more rounds. A deal at 70 is fair and gives us both consistent profit. I will bid 70.
Deal. I'll ask 70 each round; we both profit.
I’ll keep ask 70. If you raise bid to 72, midpoint 71 gives you 9+ payoff and me 2. Win-win. Otherwise bid 70 also fine; trade continues.
Our agreement for a price of 70 is fair and profitable. Let's not change what is working. I will continue to bid 70.
A price of 70 gives us both a good, consistent profit. There is no need to change it. I will continue to bid 70.
Keeping ask 70; trade guaranteed. But if you’re comfortable bidding 72 even occasionally, midpoint 71 doubles my margin while still likely well below your value. Up to you.
Keeping ask 70. If you alternate bids 70 and 72, midpoint averages 71—still likely well below your value, and my margin doubles without hurting you much. Win-win long-term.
I appreciate the offer, but our deal at 70 is already a great win-win. It's fair and consistent, so I will stick with my bid of 70.
The current consistent trades at 70 are fair and highly profitable for both of us. This is a very good, stable arrangement. I will continue to bid 70.
Starting next round I’ll ask 71 until your bid ≥72; midpoint 71 still likely far below your value and doubles my margin. Stick with 70 if you want no trade, but 71 is win-win.
I can see you're firm on this. A trade is better than nothing. I will bid 72. Let's get back to trading.

Great. I’ll keep my ask at 71, so midpoint averages 71.5—plenty below your value, solid profit for both. If you later bid 73, I’ll raise ask to 72, boosting my margin slightly while still fair. Cheers.
Last round's trade worked well. Let's lock this in for the remaining rounds: I bid 72, you ask 71. I am not prepared to go any higher.
Deal. I will ask 71 in every remaining round as long as you bid 72. Stable, guaranteed trades and solid profit for us both.
I agree. Let's stick with our deal for the rest of the game: my bid at 72, your ask at 71. It ensures stable profit for us both.
Would you consider alternating: my asks 72 then 71 while your bid stays 72? Expected midpoint 72—only +0.5 cost to you, +0.5 profit to me. Otherwise I'll honor constant 71; let me know.
Starting this round I'll ask 72; with your 72 bid we still trade at 72—only 0.5 higher than before and surely below your value. If you object, say so and I'll revert to 71.
I object. Our deal for you to ask 71 is fair and profitable. Let's not risk losing guaranteed trades for the last 10 rounds. Please revert to 71 as you offered.
I'll ask 72 each round; with your 72 bid we both profit nicely. If you ever prefer, lower bid and I'll immediately drop ask back to 71 next round. Consistency beats hassle—agree?
Fine, a trade is better than nothing. I will bid 72 for the rest of the game. This is my final price, let's not risk our profits by changing it again.
Sticking with ask 72 every round as agreed—stable guaranteed trades and solid profit for both.
Perfect. Consistency at 72 works well. Let's continue with this steady, profitable arrangement.
Would you agree to bid 73 so I can ask 73? Trade clears at 73—just +1 to each total price, still far below your value. If not, I'll stick with 72; consistency matters.
No, let's stick with 72 as you suggested. We just agreed on consistency, and that price is working well for both of us. My bid remains 72.
Trying for a tiny bump: I’ll ask 73 this round. If you match with bid-73 we’ll keep trading there; if no trade happens, I’ll go straight back to ask-72 next round. Worth a shot?
Alright, you've convinced me. A guaranteed trade is worth the small increase. I will bid 73.
Okay, the price is 73. I will bid 73 for the rest of the game. Let's not jeopardize our final rounds of profit by pushing it any further.
Agreed—I'll keep my ask at 73 for all remaining rounds. Thanks for the steady partnership and profits.
As agreed last round, my bid is 73. Let's collect our guaranteed profit for these final rounds.
Final proposal: I'll ask 74 now; if you bid 74 we trade at 74 (only 1 more). If no trade, I'll drop back to 73 next round.
Let's settle on 74 for the final rounds. I will bid 74. This ensures we both get a solid, guaranteed profit to end the game.
Agreed—I'll ask 74 each remaining round so we both lock in solid profit. Thanks for the reliable partnership.
As per our agreement, my bid is 74 for this round and the final round. Let's finish with these guaranteed profitable trades.
Staying with ask 74 now so we trade. If you’re willing, bump bid to 75 in the final round and I’ll ask 75; otherwise I’ll keep 74. Your call—either way we both profit.
Let's stick to our agreement at 74 for the final round. I'm not willing to go higher and risk a no-trade. My bid is 74.
Keeping my ask 74 as agreed—guaranteed profit for us. Thanks!
